column1: #Text=The Portland Trail Blazers ( 30 - 10 ) defeated the San Antonio Spurs ( 25 - 16 ) 110 - 96 on Wednesday at the AT & T Center in San Antonio .
#Text=The Spurs got off to a quick start in this one , out - scoring the Spurs 35 - 28 in the first quarter alone .

#Text=The Spurs were able to coast to a victory in front of their home crowd , as they shot 50 percent from the field and 38 percent from the three - point line , while the Spurs finished at 45 percent from the floor and just 32 percent from deep .
#Text=The Trail Blazers were also able to force the Spurs into 16 turnovers , while committing only 12 of their own .
#Text=The Spurs were led by the duo of LaMarcus Aldridge and LaMarcus Aldridge .
#Text=Aldridge went 9 - for - 18 from the field and 6 - for - 6 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 24 points , while also adding eight rebounds and three assists .
#Text=He 000s now averaging 25 points and 8 rebounds on the season .
#Text=Aldridge on the other hand went 9 - for - 18 from the field and 6 - for - 6 from the three - point line to score 24 points , while also adding eight rebounds and three assists .
#Text=It was his second double - double in a row , as he 000s combined for 54 points and 13 rebounds over that span .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Manu Ginobili had 13 points ( 4 - 12 FG , 1 - 6 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) and seven assists in 22 minutes .
#Text=The Spurs 000 next game will be at home against the Dallas Mavericks on Friday , while the Spurs will be at home against the Golden State Warriors on Friday .
